---
Syntax: colist

Displays a complete reference list of all available color codes. Color codes
can be used in your title, description, and anywhere the game accepts
player-formatted text.

To use a color code, type @@ followed immediately by the letter (no spaces):
  @@r  -- Red        @@g  -- Green
  @@b  -- Blue       @@y  -- Yellow
  @@c  -- Cyan       @@m  -- Magenta
  @@w  -- White      @@k  -- Dark/Black
  @@N  -- Reset to normal color
  @@W  -- Bright white (bold)

Example:  Your title set to "@@rMighty@@N Warrior" would display as:
  (red)Mighty(reset) Warrior

Color display requires the COLOR setting to be enabled. Use the CONFIG or
COLOR command to toggle color support on or off.

See also: color config title description
